# Rewrite no-trailing-slash requests to serve directory index without issuing a redirect.
# Cloudflare Pages CDN normally 301-redirects /path → /path/ for directory-based pages.
# Using status 200 (rewrite) intercepts the request BEFORE that redirect fires and serves
# the content transparently — so Google sees a clean 200 with no redirect chain.
/chimney-sweeping/:slug /chimney-sweeping/:slug/ 200
/blog /blog/ 200
/blog/:slug /blog/:slug/ 200
